Load data

amyloidbynetwork <- read_excel("~/Desktop/gmthresh_networkmsuvr.xlsx")
derivedscorecomposites <- read_csv("~/Downloads/derivedscorecomposites.csv", show_col_types = FALSE)
cogperfyear2 <- read_csv("~/Downloads/IAMY2-NPscores-composites.csv", show_col_types = FALSE)

Data wrangling

# Find tertiles
vTert = quantile(amyloidbynetwork$msuvr, probs=2/3)
# classify values (errors but still works)
amyloidbynetwork$msuvr_groups <- ifelse(amyloidbynetwork$msuvr > vTert, "AB+", "AB-")
#create AB=/AB- from neurorad read
amyloidbynetwork$pet_read <- amyloidbynetwork$pet_amyloid
amyloidbynetwork$pet_read <- ifelse(amyloidbynetwork$pet_read > 0, "AB+", "AB-")
#rearrange data frame to be long and group by network
#gather data based on network
data_long <- gather(amyloidbynetwork, key= "Network", value = "Amyloid", LIM_msuvr, DAT_msuvr, VAT_msuvr, FPN_msuvr, DMN_msuvr, VIS_msuvr, SOM_msuvr)
#make the variable "network" a factor
data_long$Network <- factor(data_long$Network)
#only include complete cases
data_long<- data_long[complete.cases(data_long),]
#make the variable "msuvr_groups" a factor
data_long$msuvr_groups<-as.factor(data_long$msuvr_groups)
#make the variable "pet_read" a factor
data_long$pet_read<-as.factor(data_long$pet_read)
#gather data based on network type- cog vs non-cog
data_long <- data_long %>%
  mutate(network_type = ifelse(Network %in% c("LIM_msuvr", "DAT_msuvr", "VAT_msuvr", "FPN_msuvr", "DMN_msuvr"), "Cognitive", "Non-Cognitive"))
# relevel networks so that Visual network will be the reference group
data_long$Network <- factor(data_long$Network, levels = c("VIS_msuvr", "SOM_msuvr", "LIM_msuvr", "VAT_msuvr", "DAT_msuvr", "FPN_msuvr", "DMN_msuvr"))
#make "network_type" into a factor
data_long$network_type<-as.factor(data_long$network_type)
data_long$network_type <- factor(data_long$network_type, levels = c("Non-Cognitive", "Cognitive"))
#remove _msuvr from variable value for network
data_long <- data_long %>%
  mutate(Network = gsub("_msuvr", "", Network))
# Group networks into cognitive and non-cognitive
cognitive_networks <- c("FPN", "DMN", "VAT", "DAT", "LIM")
non_cognitive_networks <- c("SOM", "VIS")
# Calculate the average amyloid for cognitive and non-cognitive networks for each person
averaged_data <- data_long %>%
  group_by(studyid, network_type) %>%
  summarise(avg_amyloid = mean(Amyloid)) %>%
  spread(network_type, avg_amyloid) 
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'studyid'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
#add in cognitive data
merged_data0 <- merge(averaged_data, derivedscorecomposites, by = "studyid", all = FALSE)
merged_data <- merge(merged_data0, amyloidbynetwork, by = "studyid", all = FALSE)
cogperfyear2$studyid <- sub("b$", "", cogperfyear2$studyid)  # Remove the trailing "b"
# Merge with custom suffixes for year 2 data
merged_data <- merged_data %>%
  full_join(cogperfyear2, by = "studyid", suffix = c("", ".year2"))
#create difference score between year 0 and year 2 cognitive scores
merged_data$gencomp_adjz_diff <- merged_data$gencomp_adjz.year2 - merged_data$gencomp_adjz
gencomp_df<-merged_data [, c("studyid", "gencomp_adjz", "gencomp_adjz_diff")]
# Merge gencomp_data into data_long by studyid
data_long <- data_long %>%
  left_join(gencomp_df, by = "studyid")
#merge averaged data into data_long
data_long <- data_long %>%
  left_join(averaged_data, by = "studyid")

Test for differences between non-cognitive and cognitive amyloid in whole sample with LMM

# Fit the linear mixed-effects model
# Amyloid_network is the dependent variable
# NetworkType (Cognitive/Non-Cognitive) is the fixed effect
# (1 | Participant) models random intercepts for each Participant
# age as fixed effect 
model1 <- lmerTest::lmer(Amyloid ~ network_type + age + (1 | studyid), data = data_long)
#omnibus test
# Fit the null model (without fixed effects)
null_model <- lmer(Amyloid ~ (1 | studyid), data = data_long, REML = FALSE)
# Conduct a likelihood ratio test comparing the full and null model
anova(null_model, model1)

Test for differences between non-cognitive and cognitive amyloid in whole sample with ttest

# Run the paired t-test comparing cognitive and non-cognitive networks
t_test_result <- t.test(averaged_data$Cognitive, averaged_data$'Non-Cognitive', paired = TRUE)
# Print the results
print(t_test_result)

Plot for differences between non-cognitive and cognitive amyloid in whole sample

ggplot(data_long, aes(x = network_type, y = Amyloid, fill = network_type)) +
  geom_line(aes(group = studyid), color = "grey", alpha = 0.5) +  # Connect cognitive and non-cognitive for the same person
  geom_point(position = position_jitterdodge(seed = 4), 
             aes(color = network_type), 
             alpha = 0.25, size = 2, shape = 21, stroke = 0.5) +  # Scatter plot with matching color and small outline
  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.5, outlier.shape=NA) +  # Boxplot for cognitive vs. non-cognitive networks
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("#4D4D4D", "#FF4500")) +  # Ensure fill color matches the network type
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#4D4D4D", "#FF4500")) +  # Ensure dot color matches the network type
  ggtitle("Amyloid Levels in Cognitive vs Non-Cognitive Networks") +  # Title of the plot
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),  # Center title
        panel.background = element_blank(),  # Remove background
        legend.position = "none") +  # Remove legend if not needed
  xlab("Network Type") +  # X-axis label
  ylab("Amyloid Burden (msuvr)")  # Y-axis label

Test effect of network (7) on amyloid in whole sample with LMM

# Fit the linear mixed-effects model
# Amyloid_network is the dependent variable
# Network is the fixed effect
# (1 | Participant) models random intercepts for each Participant
# Age is a fixed effect (covariate)
model4 <- lmerTest::lmer(Amyloid ~ Network + age + (1 | studyid), data = data_long, REML=TRUE)
anova(model4)
## Type III Analysis of Variance Table with Satterthwaite's method
##         Sum Sq Mean Sq NumDF DenDF F value  Pr(>F)    
## Network 1.0629 0.17715     6   936  41.154 < 2e-16 ***
## age     0.1046 0.10460     1   155  24.299 2.1e-06 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
#omnibus test
# Fit the null model (without fixed effects)
null_model <- lmer(Amyloid ~ (1 | studyid), data = data_long, REML = FALSE)
# Conduct a likelihood ratio test comparing the full and null model
anova(null_model, model4)
## refitting model(s) with ML (instead of REML)

#table of anova results
# Create a data frame with your ANOVA results
anova_results <- data.frame(
  Source = c("Network", "Age"),
  Sum_Sq = c(1.0629, 0.1046),
  Mean_Sq = c(0.17715, 0.10460),
  NumDF = c(6, 1),
  DenDF = c(936, 155),
  F_value = c(41.154, 24.299),
  Pr_greater_than_F = c("< 2e-16", "2.1e-06"),
  Significance = c("***", "***")
)
kable(anova_results, format = "html", digits = 3, 
      col.names = c("Source", "Sum Sq", "Mean Sq", "Num DF", "Den DF", "F Value", "Pr(>F)", "Significance")) %>%
  kable_styling("striped", full_width = F) %>%
  add_header_above(c(" " = 1, "Type III ANOVA Results" = 7))

# Define the colors for networks
network_colors <- c(
  "SOM" = "lightblue", 
  "LIM" = "yellow", 
  "VAT" = "magenta", 
  "DAT" = "green", 
  "FPN" = "orange", 
  "DMN" = "red", 
  "VIS" = "purple"
)

# Function to adjust colors
adjusted_colors <- function(base_color) {
  # Darker version
  darker_color <- adjustcolor(base_color, alpha.f = 1)  # No transparency
  # Lighter version
  lighter_color <- adjustcolor(base_color, alpha.f = 0.3)  # 50% transparency
  return(c(darker = darker_color, lighter = lighter_color))
}

# Create a named vector for the adjusted colors, matching the levels correctly
adjusted_color_palette <- unlist(lapply(names(network_colors), function(n) {
  colors <- adjusted_colors(network_colors[n])
  setNames(colors, c(paste0(n, ".AB+"), paste0(n, ".AB-")))  # Use . instead of _
}))

# Check the levels in data_long for interaction
data_long$interaction <- interaction(data_long$Network, data_long$pet_read)

# Use ggplot with the custom color mapping
ggplot(data_long, aes(x = Network, y = Amyloid, color = interaction)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  geom_point(position = position_jitterdodge(seed = 4), aes(color = interaction)) +
  scale_color_manual(values = adjusted_color_palette) +  # Use adjusted colors
  ggtitle("Amyloid by Network") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), 
        panel.background = element_blank(), 
        legend.position = "bottom") +
  xlab("Network") +
  ylab("Amyloid") +
  labs(color = 'Preclinical AD Status')

Correlate cognitive amyloid and general cognitive composite (baseline)

# Calculate correlation spearman
correlation_result <- cor.test(merged_data$Cognitive, merged_data$gencomp_adjz, method = "spearman")
print(correlation_result)
## 
##  Spearman's rank correlation rho
## 
## data:  merged_data$Cognitive and merged_data$gencomp_adjz
## S = 639656, p-value = 0.7045
## alternative hypothesis: true rho is not equal to 0
## sample estimates:
##         rho 
## -0.03067255
#plot
ggplot(data = merged_data, aes(x = Cognitive, y = gencomp_adjz)) +
  geom_point(size = 2) +  # Scatter points

  labs(
    title = "Scatter Plot",
    x = "Cognitive Amyloid",
